### Flag 2 — Initial Access: Compromised Account

The account used throughout the attack was `kenji.sato`, a domain account on the `azuki-sl` machine. This account was present in every initial access, discovery, and staging activity and was the account whose credentials were subsequently dumped from LSASS memory for use in lateral movement.

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Answer** | `kenji.sato` |
| **Account Domain** | azuki-sl |
| **SID** | S-1-5-21-3215208035-5178038... |
| **Action Type** | LogonSuccess |

**KQL Query:**
```kql
DeviceLogonEvents
| where DeviceName == "azuki-sl"
| where LogonType == "RemoteInteractive"
| where Timestamp > ago(300d)
| project Timestamp, AccountName, AccountDomain, RemoteIP, ActionType
| sort by Timestamp asc
```

