### Flag 4 — Defence Evasion: Malware Staging Directory

The attacker created a hidden directory to organise downloaded tools and stage data prior to exfiltration. The directory was named to resemble a legitimate Windows cache folder and was immediately hidden and marked as a system folder using built-in Windows attribute commands.

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Answer** | `C:\ProgramData\WindowsCache` |
| **File Name** | attrib.exe |
| **Full Command** | `"attrib.exe" +h +s C:\ProgramData\WindowsCache` |
| **Effect** | Directory hidden from standard browsing and protected from casual deletion |
| **Timestamp** | Nov 19, 2025 — 19:05:33 UTC |

**KQL Query:**
```kql
DeviceProcessEvents
| where DeviceName == "azuki-sl"
| where Timestamp > datetime(2025-11-19T18:36:00)
| where ProcessCommandLine contains "mkdir"
   or ProcessCommandLine contains "New-Item"
   or ProcessCommandLine contains "attrib"
| project Timestamp, FileName, ProcessCommandLine, AccountName
| sort by Timestamp asc
```

