### Flag 8 — Persistence: Scheduled Task Name

To survive system reboots and maintain reliable access, the attacker created a scheduled task that re-executes the malware implant automatically. The task was given a name designed to appear as routine Windows maintenance.

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Answer** | `Windows Update Check` |
| **Full Command** | `schtasks.exe /create /tn "Windows Update Check" /tr C:\ProgramData\WindowsCache\svchost.exe /sc daily /st 02:00 /ru SYSTEM /f` |
| **Schedule** | Daily at 02:00 |
| **Run As** | SYSTEM |
| **Timestamp** | Nov 19, 2025 — 19:07:46 UTC |

Running as SYSTEM grants the task the highest available privilege level on the machine. A second scheduled task was also identified later in the timeline (Nov 25) pointing to `C:\Windows\Temp\silentlynx.exe` under the task name `Microsoft\Windows\Security\SecurityHealthService` — a second persistence mechanism added as the attacker expanded their foothold.

**KQL Query:**
```kql
DeviceProcessEvents
| where DeviceName == "azuki-sl"
| where Timestamp > datetime(2025-11-19T18:36:00)
| where FileName == "schtasks.exe"
| where ProcessCommandLine contains "/create"
| project Timestamp, FileName, ProcessCommandLine
| sort by Timestamp asc
```

