### Flag 10 — Command and Control: C2 Server Address

After the malicious `svchost.exe` payload was executed, it established an outbound connection to the attacker's command and control server. The same IP address that hosted the malware downloads was also receiving C2 beacon traffic from the implant — a common pattern where attackers consolidate download and C2 infrastructure on a single server.

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Answer** | `78.141.196.6` |
| **Initiating Process** | svchost.exe (malicious) |
| **Remote Port** | 443 |
| **First Beacon** | Nov 19, 2025 — 19:11:04 UTC |
| **Last Seen** | Nov 19, 2025 — 19:11:04 UTC (in this dataset) |

**KQL Query:**
```kql
DeviceNetworkEvents
| where DeviceName == "azuki-sl"
| where Timestamp > datetime(2025-11-19T18:36:00)
| where InitiatingProcessFileName in ("svchost.exe", "AdobeGC.exe", "mm.exe")
| where RemoteIP !startswith "10."
| where RemoteIP !startswith "192.168"
| summarize ConnectionCount = count(),
            FirstSeen = min(Timestamp),
            LastSeen = max(Timestamp)
            by RemoteIP, RemotePort, InitiatingProcessFileName
| sort by ConnectionCount desc
```

