### Flag 11 — Command and Control: C2 Communication Port

The malware communicated with the C2 server over port 443, deliberately blending its traffic with normal HTTPS web browsing. This technique makes C2 traffic significantly harder to detect or block without SSL/TLS inspection capabilities at the network perimeter.

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Answer** | `443` |
| **Protocol** | HTTPS |
| **Significance** | Encrypted, indistinguishable from normal web traffic without deep packet inspection |

This answer was identified from the same result row as Flag 10 — a reminder that efficient hunters extract maximum intelligence from every query result.

