As a secondary persistence mechanism, the attacker created a local user account named `support` and added it to the local administrators group. This provides a fallback access method that survives a password reset on the `kenji.sato` account and would appear to any administrator reviewing the user list as a legitimate helpdesk or IT support account.

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Answer** | `support` |
| **Full Command** | `"net.exe" user support ********** /add` |
| **Confirmed By** | net1.exe executing the same command simultaneously |
| **Timestamp** | Nov 19, 2025 — 19:09:48 UTC |
| **Technique** | Create Account: Local Account (T1136.001) |

**KQL Query:**
```kql
DeviceProcessEvents
| where DeviceName == "azuki-sl"
| where Timestamp > datetime(2025-11-19T18:36:00)
| where FileName == "net.exe" or FileName == "net1.exe"
| project Timestamp, FileName, ProcessCommandLine
| sort by Timestamp asc
```

